cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.COM, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the role of resource pooling in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the mechanisms for shifting load between different parts of the unified resource pool, which is related to information theory and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also discusses the resilience and security of wireless networks, which is related to computer security (cs.CR) and communication and information theory (cs.COM). Finally, the paper discusses the applications of resource pooled wireless technologies, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
